  "texts": [
    "One can understand this choice by considering the longest vector in a unit hypercube, which is the diagonal vector that connects two opposite vertices and passes through the center.",
    "For a hypercube of positive values with side ρ, the magnitude of the diagonal vector is",
    "Hence, given a hypercube of continuous numbers with side ρ = 1, dividing each vector in the space by √ d k normalizes their magnitude to unity.",
    "The dot product of a diagonal vector with itself is equal to the square of its magnitude.",
    "Therefore, the dot product of a magnitude normalized diagonal vector with itself is unity."
  ],
